title.narrative: CROSS-SECTORAL APPROACHES

description.narrative: Strategies to address cross-cutting issues related to child rights are developed and applied, which contributes to Cross-Sectoral Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Cross-Sectoral Planning And Programme Reviews, Disaster Risk Reduction, Disaster Risk Reduction (Covid), Gender Discriminatory Roles And Practices, Operations Support To Programme Delivery, Other Cross-Sectoral Programme Areas, Supply And Logistics. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Operational Support To Programme Delivery. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Programmes are efficiently designed, coordinated, managed and supported to meet quality programming standards in achieving results for children in development and humanitarian setting.

description.narrative: The first year of the Government of the Philippines-UNICEF 8th Country Programme and United Nations Partnership Framework for Sustainable Development focused on operationalizing programme change strategies and strengthening the principles of inclusion and preparedness for humanitarian situations. Ten humanitarian responses were supported and the level of emergency preparedness across all results were strengthened. UNICEF demonstrated leadership in the Prevention of Sexual Exploitation and Abuse within the UN and particularly within the UN Humanitarian Country Team. New programme coordination and governance mechanisms were established, or existing mechanisms strengthened. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:07/02/2020
